Add support for multiple teams with the same primary name (issue #77)

Let --team accept a team name or id

We can't rely on the team name to be unique, so we allow an id to be
specified. The id is printed along with the name in the list of options.
The beginning of the team name is still accepted.

Fix the --team option to accept the team name

Two issues were fixed here:
- Passing the --team option did not skip the "Select a team:" prompt.
- The --team option should accept the name of the team. Not the value of
  the radio button associated to the team.

Merge pull request #23 from subblue/master

Fix SSL errors on ruby 1.9.x

Added the 'certified' gem to prevent SSL errors on ruby 1.9.x such as 'error: SSL_connect returned=1 errno=0 state=SSLv3 read server certificate B: certificate verify failed.' as described on http://martinottenwaelter.fr/2010/12/ruby19-and-the-ssl-error/
